AB  - To address urban parking challenges arising from increasing vehicle ownership and limited space for new developments, we propose a blockchain-powered parking reservation system. This system enables private parking spaces to be shared during unused times, helping to alleviate issues such as illegal parking and congestion. It takes into account important factors like proximity to the city center, cleanliness, security, and the availability of electric vehicle (EV) charging points, which have become crucial with the growing adoption of EVs. Using a multi-criteria decision-making method, it ranks parking options based on user preferences, assigning the best match or recommending alternatives if the preferred spot is unavailable. Additionally, a Bayesian average rating algorithm updates parking ratings based on user feedback, improving the experience for future users. Blockchain integration ensures automation, reduces operational costs and guarantees transparency and immutability. This innovative approach maximizes the utilization of existing parking resources and offers a secure, efficient, and user-centric solution to urban parking issues while contributing to sustainable city development.
