AB  - As the Internet of Energy (IoE) network expands, integrating Electric Vehicles (EVs) into decentralized energy systems is essential for a secure and sustainable low-carbon future. However, EV adoption faces challenges such as limited driving range and inadequate charging infrastructure, particularly in rural and highway areas. This paper presents a blockchain-enabled framework for secure Vehicle-to-Vehicle (V2V) and Vehicle-to-Grid (V2G) energy trading, enhancing energy flexibility within the Carbon-Intelligent IoE. The framework optimizes trading strategies, ensures fairness, and stabilizes the grid by incorporating key game-theoretic models, Contract Theory, Bayesian Game Theory, and Evolutionary Game Theory, which are central to the proposed energy trading mechanism. Built on a lightweight Hyperledger Fabric architecture, the framework enables secure, transparent, and cost-efficient transactions. Performance evaluations show high efficiency, with transaction throughputs of 49.8 TPS for payments, 44.7 TPS for energy trades, and an average latency of 0.09-0.18 seconds. Resource utilization analysis indicates an average CPU usage of 23.76% and memory consumption of 169.5 MB during trade proposals. These results demonstrate the framework's scalability, security, and robustness in enabling decentralized, carbon-intelligent energy trading within the IoE, advancing next-generation smart energy ecosystems.
